# Dockerfile - repository-visible devcontainer image extension
#
# Why this exists:
# - `initialize.sh` copies this file to `.codegeist/Dockerfile` when missing.
# - The root `.codegeist/Dockerfile` is appended to the kit base Dockerfile when
#   `.devcontainer/Dockerfile.merged.gen` is generated.
# - This is an extension fragment, not a full Dockerfile; do not add a base image
#   instruction.
#
# Related files:
# - initialize.sh
# - Dockerfile.base
# - .codegeist/Dockerfile

# Add repository-specific devcontainer image extensions here, for example:
# USER root
# RUN npm install -g some-coding-agent-tool
# USER ${CONTAINER_USER}
